article.headline: VMI 79, Liberty 78
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Reggie Williams hit the winning lay-up with 1:09 to play and VMI hung on to beat Liberty 79-78 in the first round of the Big South tournament Tuesday night. VMI (12-18, 5-9) led 44-38 at the break, but Liberty started the second half with a 16-7 run to retake the lead 54-51 with 13:30 remaining. No. 3 seeded Liberty (14-16, 8-6) led by five with 5:05 to play, but VMI outscored the Flames 10-4 the rest of the way. The teams went back and forth for the final three minutes. After Williams' lay-up, conference scoring leader Larry Blair missed two 3-pointers -- the Flames' only two shot attempts in the game's final minute. Blair's final shot with 1 second left hit the back end of the rim. Williams scored 23 points and grabbed nine rebounds while Matt Murrer had 21 points and 11 rebounds for No. 6 seed VMI. Travis Holmes added 16 points and Chavis Holmes had 13, as VMI shot 51.6 percent. Blair scored 17, Dwight Brewington had 15, Tyler Baker 12 and Anthony Smith 10 for the Flames, which shot 46.6 percent. VMI advances to play No. 2 seed High Point in Thursday's semifinals.
